  "text": "Proof: Without loss of generality, suppose one base i has coordinates x i = (0, 0). Let Ω 0 = {x γ |x γ ∈ D G0 U(x) ≤ U(x 0 )}. Ω 0 is closed and bounded by r = |G|∆. SinceU = − ∂U ∂x T ∂U ∂x ≤ 0, then by LaSalle's invariance principle [CITATION_1] every solution converges to M . Furthermore since wheneverU = 0, thenẋ = 0, it follows that any x ∈ M is a £xed point.",
